            {
                "numero": 2,
                "titre": "Step 2: Eureka Moment",
                "solutions": [
                    {
                        "objectif": "",
                        "materiaux_outils": [],
                        "etapes": [
                            {
                                "titre": "I still wanted to magnetize my pencils, the key ingredients being a pencil- a magnet and something rubbery or flexible between. That's when it occurred to me to use heat shrink electrical tube!",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "Initially I thought the tube wouldn't seal around the pencil end so I used an M8 nut to thread the end to create a more grippy surface (weird I know but why not). You can jump this stage as it seems to to hold just fine without it - unless you have particularly slippery pencils!",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "Cut some heat shrink - approx.50-60mm",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "For the magnets I had some rectangular ones that were broken in half as well as disc ones.",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "Basically assemble together - push the tube over the pencil end approx.20mm, push the magnet in but leave a gap. You want to end up with enough gap in the tube so it seals up around the magnet at both ends.",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "To be honest you can experiment to what suits you but I like the flex this gives.",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            }
                        ],
