                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "But here's some pictures of examples. We also have one on the fridge door - just need a magnetic note book...",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "I never did examples of pens but the principles the same. You could also use different colour heat shrink to indicate if the pencil is a harder composition, for example 3H or softer like 2B (if you use different ones). Also the advantage of the plastic covering the magnet if it ever picks up metal filings its a lot easier to remove than direct to the magnet.",
